						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kongu, Vīrakēraḷa Amarabhujamgavarman, Year 28 = c.11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>In Vaṭṭeḻuttucharacters. Mutilated at the end. Records a sale of land by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of some Chaturvēdimaṅgalam to Sundarachōḻa-māyilaṭṭi, a native of Kāṭṭagam in Puṟangarambai-nāḍu. The latter seems to have gifted the land to the temple of Tiruvarāl-ūr. The gift was to be protected by the army people <hi rend="italic">mūlabalattār</hi> and <hi rend="italic">agrattoṭi-paḍaiyār.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
